🔹 Spark SQL
Explanation

“Spark SQL in Apache Spark is a module that allows processing structured and semi-structured data using SQL queries, DataFrames, and Datasets, 
with built-in optimization through the Catalyst Optimizer.”

Code
✔ Create DataFrame and Temp View
df.createOrReplaceTempView("orders")
✔ Run SQL Query
spark.sql("SELECT customer_id, SUM(amount) as total FROM orders GROUP BY customer_id").show()

