🔹 How to register temp table (Temp View)
Explanation

“In Apache Spark, a temporary view can be created from a DataFrame using createOrReplaceTempView, allowing SQL queries to be executed on that DataFrame within the same session.”

Code
df.createOrReplaceTempView("orders")

spark.sql("SELECT * FROM orders").show()

3..
🔹 Temp View vs Global Temp View
Explanation

“Temp views are session-scoped and accessible only within the current Spark session, whereas global temp views are application-scoped and 
accessible across multiple sessions using a system-defined database.”

Code
# Temp View
df.createOrReplaceTempView("orders")

# Global Temp View
df.createOrReplaceGlobalTempView("global_orders")

# Access global temp view
spark.sql("SELECT * FROM global_temp.global_orders").show()


