How Spark Executes SQL Query
Explanation

“In Apache Spark, when a SQL query is executed, Spark converts it into a logical plan, optimizes it using the Catalyst Optimizer, transforms it into a physical plan, and then executes it as distributed tasks across executors.”

Code
df.createOrReplaceTempView("orders")

spark.sql("""
SELECT customer_id, SUM(amount) as total
FROM orders
GROUP BY customer_id
""").show()
Execution Flow (Important)
SQL Query
   ↓
Logical Plan
   ↓ (Catalyst Optimizer)
Optimized Logical Plan
   ↓
Physical Plan
   ↓
Job → Stages → Tasks → Execution

