“A CTE (Common Table Expression) in Spark SQL is a temporary named result set defined using the WITH clause, which can be referenced within a 
query to simplify complex SQL logic.”

Code
spark.sql("""
WITH sales_cte AS (
    SELECT customer_id, SUM(amount) as total
    FROM orders
    GROUP BY customer_id
)
SELECT * FROM sales_cte WHERE total > 1000
""").show()

