🔹 Subquery Support in Spark SQL
Explanation

“In Apache Spark, subquery support refers to the ability to use a query inside another SQL query, allowing complex filtering and transformations using nested queries.”

Types of Subqueries
🔹 1. Scalar Subquery

Returns a single value.

spark.sql("""
SELECT name
FROM orders
WHERE amount > (SELECT AVG(amount) FROM orders)
""").show()
🔹 2. Correlated Subquery

Depends on outer query values.

spark.sql("""
SELECT o1.name
FROM orders o1
WHERE amount > (
    SELECT AVG(o2.amount)
    FROM orders o2
    WHERE o1.customer_id = o2.customer_id
)
""").show()
🔹 3. IN / EXISTS Subquery
spark.sql("""
SELECT *
FROM orders
WHERE customer_id IN (
    SELECT customer_id FROM orders WHERE amount > 1000
)
""").show()


